3. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper proposes a Lipschitz Optimization scheme to solve the Threshold Activation Problem under DIP, which can be seen as a control problem. 
4. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) - The paper discusses the complexity of the Threshold Activation Problem under DIP and proposes an algorithm to solve it, which falls under the subfield of data structures and algorithms. 
5. cs.CY (Computational Geometry) - The Lipschitz Optimization scheme proposed in the paper involves optimization over a continuous space, which can be seen as a computational geometry problem.
